This paper is about optimizing machine learning algorithms for energy efficiency, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The specific algorithm being optimized is a data stream mining algorithm, which could also fall under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and energy consumption, which is a common theme in "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results, which could be considered "Data Mining" (cs.DM) or "Software Engineering" (cs.SE) depending on the focus of the experiments.
